				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/adminbright" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(224440); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=224440&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610249171" alt="AdminBright" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=224440)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/adminbright" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(224440); return false;" >AdminBright</a></span> <span class="odate time_1315847336 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">12 Sep 2011 17:08</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1256782">
									

<p>See, the point in keeping things is that the Foundation is pack rats. one day, these things will come in handy. Do we use them right now? probably not. But, one day, there might be a use, even if its just to deal with other SCPs. and, mostly, the idea is that the Foundation contains things. It's what we do, who we are, we contain them. If the best way to contain something is in pieces, then yes, we'll take that route.</p>

							</div>

										<div class="signature">
					<hr class="signature-separator"/>
					

<p>Admin, SCP Wiki</p>

